More properties
===============
The fourier transform of $h(t)$ is $H(\omega)$

$h(t-\tau) \leftrightarrow e^{j\omega t}H(j\omega)$

$h(t)*x(t) \leftrightarrow H(j\omega)X(j\omega)$
$\int_{-\infty}^{\infty} \int_{-\infty}^{\infty} (h(t-\tau)x(\tau) d\tau)e^{-j\omega t} dt$
$=\int_{-\infty}^{\infty} x(\tau) \int_{-\infty}^{\infty} h(t-\tau)e^{-j\omega t} dt d\tau$
$=X(j\omega)H(j\omega)$

$\frac{dX(t)}{dt} \leftrightarrow j\omega X(j\omega)$
$-j tx(t) \leftrightarrow \frac{dX(j\omega)}{d\omega}$

$e^{j\omega_0 t}x(t) \leftrightarrow X(j(\omega-\omega_0))$

Amplitude Modulation (AM)
=========================
$s(t)$ --> $\boxed{\times cos(\omega_c t)}$ -$r(t)$->  Transmission

$R(t)=\frac{1}{2}(S(j(\omega-\omega_0))+S(j(\omega+\omega_0)))$

Frequency Response of CT LTI Systems
====================================

$a_0y(t) + a_1y'(t)+\cdots = b_0x(t)+b_1x'(y)+\cdots$
$\sum_{k=0}^{N} a_k \frac{d^k}{dt^k}y(t)=\sum_{k=0}^{N} b_k \frac{d^k}{dt^k}x(t)$
$\leftrightarrow \sum_{k=0}^{N} a_k(j\omega)^k Y(j\omega)=\sum_{k=0}^{N} b_k(j\omega)^k X(j\omega)$
$\frac{Y(\omega)}{X(\omega)}=H(j\omega)=\frac{\sum_{k=0}^{N} a_k(j\omega)^k}{\sum_{k=0}^{N} b_k(j\omega)^k}$
